{
  "stem": "14060.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And a lady-- who was a spinster, I would practically describe her, certainly later on she never got married-- her name was Boros Rozsi-- came and desperately stood in front of the door and-- and kept ringing the bell.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father went down-- we lived in a house which had a mezzanine floor and had a drive in and it was like today you see in central European cities-- and asked her to come in.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So she said that terrible events are happening.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There are Jews on the border, which is literally a kilometer away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Have we got any blankets and food and whatnot?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And which we did.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And to me, it was a terrible shock.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was like something which I-- I couldn't imagine, having had an Orthodox religious upbringing, that another Orthodox person can turn up on the Shabbat in a car.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "However, these things eventually one understood what was going on.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that event is very clear in my mind, the shock of something terrible happening.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Blankets, food is needed, because people are on the border.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The rest of the week was a very traumatic, eventful week, hearing news of people being taken in Vienna to scrub the streets and so on.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Don't forget, one of our premises was a huge garage premises, which was let out to a non-Jewish garage operator.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were very friendly with them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they kept going into Austria and Vienna on business regular, practically weekly.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they themselves told us what was going on with the Jews there.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I can probably put it down to the fact that I was very young and probably psychologically it didn't affect me all that much.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I just thought it was a very exciting trouble.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Something wasn't right.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
